## Rucksack Reorganization (Puzzle 1/2)

An elf ðŸ§â€â™€ï¸ has to load all of the rucksacks with supplies for the jungle journeyðŸŒ´. Unfortunately, that Elf didn't quite follow the packing instructions ðŸ“„, and so **a few items** now **need to be rearranged**.

ðŸŽ’**Each rucksack** has **2** large **compartments**.

ðŸ¥¡All **items of a given type** are meant to go into **exactly 1** of the 2 **compartments**. 
 Every **item type is identified** by a **single letter** (case sensitive).

You have a **list of all of the items** currently in each rucksack made by the Elfs ðŸ“„ (your puzzle input). Each **line** is **rucksack**, taking into account that there are the same number of items in both compartments:

* The **first half** represent items in the **first compartment**.
* The **second half** represent items in the **second compartment**.

Example:

```
